Arsenal are prepared to sell Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang for a knockdown fee this summer, it has been claimed. The Mirror says Arsenal face a battle to keep Manchester United from poaching their own player, as the Red Devils weigh up a bid for Aubameyang. The former Dortmund striker has been linked with a move to Old Trafford, with the Gunners thought to be open to the idea of selling the 30-year-old. Arsenal have slapped a £56 million asking price on Aubameyang however, which they would look to reinvest in other areas of the squad. Arsenal’s Aubameyang looking forward to Hazard reunion in London Derby Welbeck to leave Arsenal at the end of the season - reports Barcelona to sell Dembele to Arsenal for Pogba Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin